# CSS Guidelines for AI

To avoid CSS conflicts:
- Use BEM or component-based prefixes for class names.
- Do not modify styles in global.css unless necessary.
- Avoid using `!important` unless explicitly directed.
- Prefer CSS modules or utility-first CSS like Tailwind.
- Do not create generic class names like `.button`, `.container`, or `.title`.

These rules ensure maintainability and style isolation across components.
